 The Interspeech 2025 Speech Accessibility Project (SAP) Challenge The first large-scale benchmark for dysarthric ASR using 400+ hours of impaired speech from 524 individuals with conditions like Parkinson’s, ALS, and CP. ✅ 22 teams participated : 12 outperformed Whisper-large-v2 on WER, 17 on SemScore (a semantic evaluation metric) 🥇 Best system: WER = 8.11%, SemScore = 88.44% Proud to see this dataset catalyze progress in inclusive speech tech! Mark Hasegawa-Johnson Paper 2: Retrieval of Long Audios with Complex Text Queries (LARCQ) We propose a novel pipeline combining multi-modal retrieval with ALM/LLM refining to fill the gap of complex-query-to-long-audio retrieval. We also introduce two [...] is still the best option for fact lookups, Q&A, and quick precision retrieval. 🧰 GraphRAG (e.g., Microsoft GraphRAG, LightRAG, Fast-GraphRAG, HippoRAG/HippoRAG2, RAPTOR) shows real value when tasks require: 1️⃣ Multi-hop reasoning across different documents 2️⃣ Summarizing fragmented information into coherent answers 3️⃣ Creative or structured generation (e.g., combining medical protocols with patient data, or analyzing legal cases across rulings) ⚖️ There is a trade-off: GraphRAG improves reasoning depth and reliability, but adds latency and token overhead (“prompt inflation”). 🚀 A combination of both approaches is important for systems built for knowledge domains such as healthcare, law, financial analysis, and scientific discovery, etc., where understanding relationships is just as [...] when prompted with a sensory cue. For the sake of simplicity I focus on vision only. I use @Alibaba_Qwen \"Qwen/Qwen3-4B\" as the language model and @AIatMeta \"facebook/dinov2-base\" as the vision encoder. Dataset used was 1024-sample WiT dataset. Here is how it went: 1. Encode image using the vision encoder 2. Prompt the language model to generate with a) \"caption\" b)\"imagine: caption\" c) \"imagine seeing: caption\" 3. Encoded the generations 3. Use mutual knn to showcase the alignment Mutual KNN quantifies the similarity of embeddings each in a different latent space based on their neighbours. The authors use mutual knn as a metric to showcase how close are the language and vision embeddings. Thanks to the first author @sophielwang for helping me with the effort.", "score": 0.5019781, "raw_content": "Two papers accepted at Interspeech 2025 on speech tech and ASR | Venkatesh Ravichandran posted on the topic | LinkedIn\n\n===============\n\nAgree & Join LinkedIn\n\nBy clicking Continue to join or sign in, you agree to LinkedIn’s [User Agreement](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/user-agreement?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_user-agreement), [Privacy Policy](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_privacy-policy), and [Cookie Policy](https://www.linkedin.com/legal/cookie-policy?trk=linkedin-tc_auth-button_cookie-policy).\n\n[Skip to main content](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/venkateshcr_interspeech2025-speechaccessibility-asr-activity-7332600736230383618-tz8o#main-content)[LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/?trk=public_post_nav-header-logo)\n*   [Top Content](https://www.linkedin.com/top-content?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_topContent)\n*   [People](https://www.linkedin.com/pub/dir/+/+?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_people)\n*   [Learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/search?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_learning)\n*   [Jobs](https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/search?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_jobs)\n*   [Games](https://www.linkedin.com/games?trk=public_post_guest_nav_menu_games)\n\n[Sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Fvenkateshcr_interspeech2025-speechaccessibility-asr-activity-7332600736230383618-tz8o&fromSignIn=true&trk=public_post_nav-header-signin)[Join for free](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Elinkedin%2Ecom%2Fposts%2Fvenkateshcr_interspeech2025-speechaccessibility-asr-activity-7332600736230383618-tz8o&trk=public_post_nav-header-join)\n\nTwo papers accepted at Interspeech 2025 on speech tech and ASR\n==============================================================\n\nThis title was summarized by AI from the post below.\n\n[![Image 1: Venkatesh Ravichandran](https://static.licdn.com/aero-v1/sc/h/9c8pery4andzj6ohjkjp54ma2)](https://www.linkedin.com/in/venkateshcr?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)\n\n[Venkatesh Ravichandran](https://www.linkedin.com/in/venkateshcr?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)\n\n 6mo \n\n*   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fvenkateshcr_interspeech2025-speechaccessibility-asr-activity-7332600736230383618-tz8o&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n\n🔊 Thrilled to announce that two of our papers have been accepted at [Interspeech 2025](https://au.linkedin.com/company/isca-interspeech?trk=public_post-text) ! Paper 1: The Interspeech 2025 Speech Accessibility Project (SAP) Challenge The first large-scale benchmark for dysarthric ASR using 400+ hours of impaired speech from 524 individuals with conditions like Parkinson’s, ALS, and CP. ✅ 22 teams participated : 12 outperformed Whisper-large-v2 on WER, 17 on SemScore (a semantic evaluation metric) 🥇 Best system: WER = 8.11%, SemScore = 88.44% Proud to see this dataset catalyze progress in inclusive speech tech! [Mark Hasegawa-Johnson](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mark-hasegawa-johnson-21a86825?trk=public_post-text) Paper 2: Retrieval of Long Audios with Complex Text Queries (LARCQ) We propose a novel pipeline combining multi-modal retrieval with ALM/LLM refining to fill the gap of complex-query-to-long-audio retrieval. We also introduce two new benchmarks, Clotho-LARCQ and SoundDescs-LARCQ, featuring long audios and complex queries.[Milind R.](https://www.linkedin.com/in/milindmrao?trk=public_post-text)[Ruochu Yang](https://www.linkedin.com/in/ruo