To view or add a comment, [sign in](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fpeppocola_softwareengineering-llms-machinelearning-activity-7381979941745270784-YLUT&trk=public_post_feed-cta-banner-cta)\n\n*   \n[](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/nick-kvasov_when-to-use-graphs-in-rag-a-comprehensive-activity-7378141988463800320-9GPJ)\n\n[![Image 45: View profile for Nick Kvasov](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/venkateshcr_interspeech2025-speechaccessibility-asr-activity-7332600736230383618-tz8o)](https://ae.linkedin.com/in/nick-kvasov?trk=public_post_feed-actor-image)[Nick Kvasov](https://ae.linkedin.com/in/nick-kvasov?trk=public_post_feed-actor-name)  2mo    \n\n    *   [Report this post](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fnick-kvasov_when-to-use-graphs-in-rag-a-comprehensive-activity-7378141988463800320-9GPJ&trk=public_post_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=POST&_f=guest-reporting)\n\nI’ve been exploring the benefits of GraphRAGs compared to plain vanilla RAGs, and came across an interesting new paper: “When to use Graphs in RAG”. It appears that, with current retrieval approaches, GraphRAG is not a replacement for standard RAGs; it’s a complement to standard RAG systems. 💼 Standard RAG (e.g., using FAISS, Pinecone) is still the best option for fact lookups, Q&A, and quick precision retrieval. 🧰 GraphRAG (e.g., Microsoft GraphRAG, LightRAG, Fast-GraphRAG, HippoRAG/HippoRAG2, RAPTOR) shows real value when tasks require: 1️⃣ Multi-hop reasoning across different documents 2️⃣ Summarizing fragmented information into coherent answers 3️⃣ Creative or structured generation (e.g., combining medical protocols with patient data, or analyzing legal cases across rulings) ⚖️ There is a trade-off: GraphRAG improves reasoning depth and reliability, but adds latency and token overhead (“prompt inflation”). 🚀 A combination of both approaches is important for systems built for knowledge domains such as healthcare, law, financial analysis, and scientific discovery, etc., where understanding relationships is just as important as retrieving facts. There are comparisons between specific Graph RAG frameworks, check out the article. [#RAG](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Frag&trk=public_post-text)[#GraphRAG](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fgraphrag&trk=public_post-text)[#KnowledgeGraphs](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fknowledgegraphs&trk=public_post-text)[#LLM](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fllm&trk=public_post-text)[#AIresearch](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fairesearch&trk=public_post-text)[#GenerativeAI](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fgenerativeai&trk=public_post-text)[#MachineLearning](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fmachinelearning&trk=public_post-text)[#DecisionSupport](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdecisionsupport&trk=public_post-text)[#DecisionMaking](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdecisionmaking&trk=public_post-text)[#DMSS](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdmss&trk=public_post-text)[#DSS](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fhashtag%2Fdss&trk=public_post-text)[#KnowledgeAI](https: